{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"35401828-76ee-47ec-b2bc-2e2d37990f08","content":"Run this:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis combines `dotnet watch` (hot reload — reruns on file save) with `--filter` to target only that test by name. You can also use the shorter form:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\n`Name=` does an exact match on the method name, while `FullyQualifiedName~` does a contains match (useful if you don't want to type the full namespace + class).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ba92fb09-5b6d-4a51-b4e7-b0bdd3194ab8","outputTokens":150,"requestId":"0BC5:303A77:70AA46:838337:69F0123C"},"id":"7a95c45c-b08f-4b54-b4ef-426ce55c2f32","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:49:54.120Z","parentId":"c482cfad-c5f4-462d-9038-5b1c7213b492"}
